'''公民身份'''或'''公民權'''（[[英文|英文]]：'''Citizenship'''）是一種認同或身份的形式，使個人在政治社群中取得相關的社會權利和義務<ref name="Barker2004">{{cite book|author=Chris Barker|title=文化研究: 理論與實踐|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=lcIdndXVQGEC&pg=PA476|accessdate=24 January 2013|year=2004|publisher=五南圖書出版股份有限公司|isbn=978-957-11-3732-2|pages=476–|archive-date=2015-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327004307/http://books.google.com/books?id=lcIdndXVQGEC&pg=PA476|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="公民权研究手册">{{cite book|title=公民权研究手册|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=nsqNHwAACAAJ|accessdate=24 January 2013|year=2007|publisher=浙江人民出版社|isbn=978-7-213-03507-4|archive-date=2015-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150326224511/http://books.google.com/books?id=nsqNHwAACAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>，和[[国籍|国籍]]概念不同，擁有國籍如未成年的國民可能沒有行使公民權的[[權利|權利]]及[[義務|義務]]<ref name="陈治世1990">{{cite book|author=陈治世|title=國際法|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ah8P0PjX1hsC&pg=PA208|accessdate=24 January 2013|year=1990|publisher=臺灣商務印書館|isbn=978-957-05-0188-9|pages=208–|archive-date=2015-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150326232536/http://books.google.com/books?id=ah8P0PjX1hsC&pg=PA208|dead-url=no}}</ref>，在[[宪法学|宪法学]]及[[政治學|政治學]]則指由[[法律|法律]]规范及[[政治|政治]]社群中的個人和群體的[[权利|权利]]及[[义务|义务]]關係<ref name="宪法学原理">{{cite book|title=宪法学原理|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=G1FYtz_gC5UC&pg=PA179|accessdate=24 January 2013|year=2005|publisher=中信出版社|isbn=978-7-5086-0351-3|pages=179–|archive-date=2015-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327040620/http://books.google.com/books?id=G1FYtz_gC5UC&pg=PA179|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="楚树龙唐虹2006">{{cite book|author1=楚树龙|author2=唐虹|title=政治学概论|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=zVim3oTzeAoC&pg=PA33|accessdate=24 January 2013|year=2006|publisher=清华大学出版社有限公司|isbn=978-7-302-12118-3|pages=33–|archive-date=2015-03-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150326235830/http://books.google.com/books?id=zVim3oTzeAoC&pg=PA33|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

